 The Rivers State governor, Nyesom Wike, has paid condolence visit to Adolphus Wabara, former Senate President and Secretary of the Board of Trustees, of the Peopleâ€™s Democratic Party, on the death of his wife, Felicia. Mrs Wabara passed on April 10 at an Abuja hospital after a protracted ailment. Wike was accompanied on the visit by former Governor Ibrahim Dankwambo of Gombe State, Senator Lee Maeba, Senator Aduda of the Federal Capital Territory, and former House of Representatives member, Austin Opara; among others. The Rivers State governor said that he came to condole with the former third family over the demise of their matriarch whom he described as a mother with a heart of gold. Wike, who expressed grief over the demise of the deceased, prayed to God to grant the family the fortitude to bear the pains of the sad reality. The PDP presidential hopeful also prayed for the repose of the soul of the departed. Wabara thanked Wike and his entourage for finding time to identify with his family in their moment of friendship. Describing his wife as a true companion with whom he had shared moments together, Wabara said that her demise had greatly devastated him. 